title: For Sale:  Classic Star 9mm BM model 9mm 1911 style conceal carry pistol
postcontent: I just love these old Star 1911 style pistols.  Fantastic shooters.  Absolutely fantastic to hold and shoot.  Very well made, comfortable, and accurate.  Looks alot like a 1911.  It iis a single-action semi-automatic pistol that fires the 9 mm luger (most common version) round.. It was produced by Star Bonifacio Echeverria, S.A. in Spain. Although it looks like the classic M1911, its design is different in several respects. For example, the Star does not have the 1911's grip safety. In addition, the thumb safety on the Star disengages the sear, whereas it blocks the motion of the sear on a 1911. The pistol is fed by an 8-round detachable box magazine.  Includes factory box (may or may not # match to pistol - all boxes are pretty rough shape anyway), 1 eight round mag, manual in (spanish), and cleaning rod.  Finish is about 85% on all. At the time of this listing, I have three of them.  All were believed to be made in 1977. Mechanics look excellent in all, and all appear to function well.  Although I am not sure, I think they are surplus Spanish law enforcement pistols.  Most of the production was for law enforcement and military (used in Spain, Rhodesia, and other Countries).  I actually cleaned and took one to the range a few times.  Works great.  They came with the magazine safety, which means the pistol will not fire with out the magazine loaded.  In the one I used, I disconnected that feature, and if requested, can re-engage it.  I found that feature to offer little to nothing in added safety, and to be annoying.  Combat tested design.  Small enough for conceal carry.
